The 15th edition of the annual FiRe awards was held at the Windsor Golf and Country Club hotel in Kiambu county on Friday evening. With the theme being Accountable Governance for Excellence and Reliability in Financial Reporting in East Africa , chief guest Africa at UN Global Compact chief Olajobi Makinwa, commended Kenyan companies for advancing principles of good corporate governance as well as sustainability reporting. Barclays Bank emerged overall winner out of an entry field of 399. Present were CMA chief executive Paul Muthaura, his NSE counterpart Geoffrey Odundo, ICPAK chairman Fernandes Barasa and National Treasury accountant general Bernard Ndungu.